    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1850-05-25T14:56:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1850-05-25T14:56:00-05:00" n="218"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d218">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hall</persName>, district attorney,
                        to Mr. <persName type="to">Clayton</persName> Secretary of State.</hi>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Southern District of New York, United States District
                            Attorney’s Office</hi>
                    </placeName>,<lb/>
                    <date calendar="gregorian" when="1850-05-25T15:00:00-04:56">
                        <hi rend="italic">May</hi> 25, 1850—half-past 3 p.m.</date>
                </dateline>
                <p>
                    <seg type="margin">[666]</seg>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Spanish consul is in my office, and, upon *an
                    affidavit made by him, I have just issued a warrant for the arrest of M. T.
                    Tolon.</p>
                <p>Your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>J. PRESCOTT HALL,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">United States Attorney.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>P. S.—Will the President authorize me to act under the 8th section, in order
                        to seize and detain munitions of war intended to be used in aid of the Cuban
                        expedition?</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
